Polars Library (Theory Explanation)
What is Polars?
Polars is a fast and modern DataFrame library designed for data analysis, similar to Pandas, but much faster and more memory-efficient.
Itâ€™s written in Rust (a systems programming language), but provides a Python API.

Think of Polars as:

ğŸ Pandas on steroids â€” built for speed and handling big data smoothly.

Why Polars? (Advantages)
Speed: Much faster than Pandas, especially on big datasets.

Memory Efficient: Uses less RAM.

Multithreading: Uses multiple CPU cores automatically.

Lazy Evaluation: Only computes results when needed (like Spark).

Arrow-based: Uses Apache Arrow memory format, which is modern and efficient.

